main event: A civilian spotted an olive green object the size of a wash tub, rising from the ground, descending at a slight angle, and disappearing in clouds in Litchfield, Nebraska on October 13, 1965.
interesting points: The object was partially obscured and its appearance may have been distorted by atmospheric conditions.
The object had tapered ends and a tripod effect on the bottom.
The object rose from the ground, descended, and then rapidly ascended in a northerly direction before disappearing into clouds.
The witness described the object as noiseless and moving smoothly, unlike a balloon.
sighted object: olive green object the size of a wash tub
